Substitute each $x$ into $y=\dfrac{8}{7}x-14$:<ul><li>A) $(0,	frac{8}{7})$: $\dfrac{8}{7}(0)-14=-14 
e \dfrac{8}{7}$ &mdash; eliminate.</li><li>B) $(6,9)$: $\dfrac{8}{7}(6)-14=\dfrac{48}{7}-\dfrac{98}{7}=-\dfrac{50}{7} 
e 9$ &mdash; eliminate.</li><li>C) $(14,2)$: $\dfrac{8}{7}(14)-14=16-14=2$ &mdash; matches.</li><li>D) $(15,1)$: $\dfrac{8}{7}(15)-14=\dfrac{120}{7}-\dfrac{98}{7}=\dfrac{22}{7} 
e 1$ &mdash; eliminate.</li></ul>That matches choice C &mdash; <strong>C</strong> is correct.
